Kali Linux is a Debian-based Linux distribution widely used for penetration testing and cybersecurity. Vagrant is
used to automate virtual machine deployment, while VirtualBox provides virtualization support.
This experiment demonstrates the setup of a Kali Linux virtual machine using Vagrant and VirtualBox.
Procedure
Step 1: Install VirtualBox
1. Download and install VirtualBox on Windows.
2. Complete the installation process.
Step 2: Install Vagrant
1. Download and install Vagrant.
2. Verify installation:
vagrant --version
Step 3: Create Working Directory
mkdir kali-lab
cd kali-lab
Step 4: Initialize Kali Linux Vagrant Box
vagrant init kalilinux/rolling
Step 5: Start Kali Linux VM
vagrant up
Step 6: Access Kali Linux
vagrant ssh
Step 7: Verify Kali Linux
cat /etc/os-release
Output
Kali Linux virtual machine deployed successfully
Result
Thus, Kali Linux was installed successfully using Vagrant and VirtualBox
